  "title": "QUALITY ASSURANCE/QUALITY CONTROL EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p><strong>Working Location: Near Kranji</strong><br /></p><p>Responsibilities:</p><p>-Maintain and upkeep production/training/safety-related documentation.</p><p>-Maintain and upkeep receiving records/documents and request COAs from vendors.</p><p>-Coordinate with QA/QC department to ensure operation complies with food safety (e.g., FSSC/ISO) and all regulatory requirements (e.g., SFA).</p><p>Ensure the retention samples arrangement, e.g., get from production, retention area arrangement, arrange to an external laboratory, and submit the analysis to QA for review.</p><p>-Assist in ensuring the products are traceable.</p><p>-Ensure production efficiency with minimal wastage.</p><p>-Assist in monthly pest control services.</p><p>-conduct daily inspection on receiving on raw materials, production, deliveries regulatory requirement add Halal</p><p>-Asist in food safety internal audit, customer audit, FSSC/ISO audit.</p><p>-Supporting in any ad-hoc duties as assigned by management from time to time.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Requirements:</p><p>-Minimum Diploma in Applied Science (Nutrition and Food Science) or related fields</p><p>-Basic food hygiene certification is an added advantage</p><p>-Minimum 1-year relevant working experience in food manufacturing sector</p><p>-Proficient in MS office e.g., Word, and Excel.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Remuneration:</p><p>-Basic Salary :$2500-4500 (depending on working experience)</p><p>-Working Hours: 8.30AM-6.00PM (Monday to Friday)</p><p>-Company Transport provided from Kranji Mrt</p><p>-Lunch Provided</p><p>-5 days work week</p><p>-Entitled to annual leave and medical leave benefits</p>",
